## Results

### Baseline Characteristics

A total of 3477 patients were included in the analysis, of which 1720 (0.4946793) had left hemispheric ICH. They had higher NIHSS scores, higher GCS scores, and lower rates of hypertension as compared to those with right hemispheric ICH (@tbl-1).








